Package fs.fibu2.view.render

Interface Summary
JournalModule A journal module is a generic component for editing / displaying an fsfibu2 journal.
 

Class Summary
AccountInformationListRenderer Displays an AccountInformation object by displaying its name and the names of the accounts using it
AccountListRenderer Renders account list cells by simply inserting the name of the account
BilancialPanel The bilancial panel is used in Journal table views to indicate the bilancials of either all the displayed data or a certain selection.
BilancialTableRenderer This class renders money cells for a BilancialTableModel.
BilancialTree This is a JTree using a BilancialTreeModel and a BilancialTreeRenderer.
BilancialTreeRenderer For any BilancialTreeModel.ExtendedCategory as value, displays the tail of the associated category (in brackets, if it is the additional node).
CategoryEditor This class implements a short dialog for creating a new category
CategoryListRenderer Renders cells of a category list.
EntryDialog This class implements a dialog for editing / creating fsfibu2 journal Entrys.
EntryDialogFactory This class creates EntryDialogs.
FilterListRenderer Renders EntryFilter entries in lists simply by displaying the name of the filter
FilterPoolRenderer Displays an entry of a FilterPoolModel.
JournalExportRenderer Renders a JournalExport by displaying its name
JournalModuleLoader This class handles loading of JournalModule objects by ID.
JournalTable This class implements a JTable with a few general settings useful for displaying fsfibu2 Journals, as well as some more type-specific methods for model retrieval and such
JournalTableBar This class implements a toolbar with basic operations for a JournalTable, such as entry editing and view preferences, as well as a little component indicating when the table is recalculated.
JournalTableLabel This class provides a label with default colors and borders for a JournalTableRenderer.
JournalTableRenderer This class renders cells in a table with a JournalTableModel.
MoneyCellRenderer Renders a cell with a float value with an adjoint currency symbol and in red or black color depending on whether the value is < 0
ReadingPointDialog Implements a dialog for editing ReadingPoints.
ReadingPointRenderer Renders a reading point by displaying its name and its date
SeparatorRenderer Displays EntrySeparators simply by displaying their name
StartValueDialog A simple dialog containing a table for editing account start values.
YearListRenderer This class renders cells for a YearListModel, by diplaying Integers as themselves, null as a 'All years' string and everything else using toString()
